  "body": "Looking at the code (https://github.com/vitessio/vitess/blob/master/go/vt/vttablet/tabletmanager/rpc_query.go#L47 for ExecuteFetchAsDba), we just pass the bare name of the underlying database/schema to a `USE` statement.\r\n\r\nThis ends up failing (quietly, because of the way the code works) if the database name needs escaping with backticks (e.g. has dashes in it).  The result will be something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror: rpc error: code = Unknown desc = No database selected (errno 1046) (sqlstate 3D000) during query: CREATE TABLE ....\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhen you try and use ExecuteFetchAsDba to create a table against a tablet that is using an external database/schema with a name that needs escaping.\r\n\r\nThis also affects things like vtctlclient MoveTables and Materialize, since they use ExecuteFetchAsDba to copy table DDL, etc.",
